<paragraph id="E97036DD3F66FFF1FF76F831FA7DF814" blockId="83.[151,1437,1975,2037]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
Size. Maximum size about 
<quantity id="2E379B383F66FFF1FE28F831FDE0F830" box="[457,512,1975,2001]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" unit="cm" value="3.0">3 cm</quantity>
total length. Morphology. D VI + I,6–7; A I,5–7; P 15. Body slender, laterally compressed. Head long, slightly depressed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F61FFF6FF76FF10FB01FCD8" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F61FFF6FF76FF10FB4AFEFC" blockId="84.[151,1437,150,826]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FF76FF10FD1DFF51" bold="true" box="[151,765,150,177]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Snout pointed, equal to or longer than eye diameter</emphasis>
. S 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FCFAFF11FAF1FF50" bold="true" box="[795,1297,150,177]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">econd dorsal and anal fins with short base</emphasis>
and low ray counts (see fin meristics). Caudal peduncle slender, lower than body depth. Dorsal fins of similar height, first dorsal fin with more or less rounded margin. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FDB5FF58FCA3FF18" bold="true" box="[596,835,222,249]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Caudal fin truncate</emphasis>
(Kovačić 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FC5DFF59FC0FFF18" box="[956,1007,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2016; Engin 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FB75FF59FB27FF18" box="[1172,1223,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2017; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F61FFF6FAC1FF59FEDAFEFC" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Glavicic, I." pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="181 - 184" refId="ref58727" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Glavicic, I. (2019) The first Adriatic finding of Speleogobius llorisi (Actinopterygii: Gobiiformes: Gobiidae). Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 49 (2), 181 - 184. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIEP / 02540" type="journal article" year="2019">Kovačić &amp; Glavičić 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Scales present on body and on predorsal area, poorly visible on photographs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F61FFF6FF26FEA1FD14FDDC" blockId="84.[151,1437,150,826]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
Live coloration. The general hue may vary from beige to brown to reddish brown depending on the environment and the fish’s mood. Predorsal area reddish brown to whitish brown, 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FC73FECCFF5FFE68" bold="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">underside of head, cheek and opercle mostly red</emphasis>
with poorly visible white parts (Engin 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FD67FEE9FD5AFE68" box="[646,698,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2017), occasionally also yellowish (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F61FFF6FB85FEE9FA71FE68" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Glavicic, I." box="[1124,1425,367,393]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="181 - 184" refId="ref58727" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Glavicic, I. (2019) The first Adriatic finding of Speleogobius llorisi (Actinopterygii: Gobiiformes: Gobiidae). Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 49 (2), 181 - 184. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIEP / 02540" type="journal article" year="2019">Kovačić &amp; Glavičić 2019</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FF76FE15FC24FE4C" bold="true" box="[151,964,402,429]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Three dark bars on dorsal half of body, alternating with 4 pale areas</emphasis>
, these 3 bars connected to 4 dark blotches on lower side of body, one more midlateral blotch on the posterior ventral part of caudal peduncle (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F61FFF6FB2FFE31FEF0FE14" author="Duhau-Spielmann, M. &amp; Renoult, J. &amp; Louisy, P." pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refId="ref53650" refString="Duhau-Spielmann, M., Renoult, J. &amp; Louisy, P. (2021) Signalisation de / Record of Speleogobius llorisi, 04 January 2021 (obs. 03 September 2020, photo  5836). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.). Available from: https: // www. fishwatch. org (accessed 4 August 2021)" type="url" year="2021">
Duhau-Spielmann 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FF76FE5DFF29FE14" box="[151,201,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F61FFF6FEC9FE5DFE9BFE14" box="[296,379,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,980,1004]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,956]" captionTargetId="figure-19@20.[151,1436,181,956]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Speleogobius llorisi. Photo by R. Tournier-Broer, Saint-Raphaël, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601605" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601605/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FE71FE5CFBD2FE14" bold="true" box="[400,1074,474,501]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Caudal peduncle uniformly pale dorsally, dark ventrally</emphasis>
. Dark bars and blotches may be quite diffuse in males, resulting in most of the body being rather uniformly dark, except caudal peduncle dorsally. Dorsal fins with a wide beige to whitish outer margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F61FFF6FF26FDC1FD6EFD80" blockId="84.[151,1437,150,826]" box="[199,654,583,609]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F61FFF6FE9EFDC1FD67FD80" authorityName="Zander &amp; Jelinek" authorityYear="1976" box="[383,647,583,609]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Speleogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trigloides">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FE9EFDC1FD67FD80" box="[383,647,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Speleogobius trigloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F61FFF6FF26FDEDFE5BFD2F" blockId="84.[151,1437,150,826]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
Habitat. Circalittoral species, known from 
<quantity id="2E379B383F61FFF6FD48FDEDFCECFD64" box="[681,780,619,645]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05" metricValueMax="6.9" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" unit="m" value="50.5" valueMax="69.0" valueMin="32.0">32–69 m</quantity>
depth on rhodolith beds or detritic coarse sand and gravel (Kovačić 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FEE8FD09FEDEFD48" box="[265,318,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2016; Engin 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FE09FD09FDFDFD48" box="[488,541,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2017; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F61FFF6FD9BFD09FC48FD48" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Glavicic, I." box="[634,936,655,681]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="181 - 184" refId="ref58727" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Glavicic, I. (2019) The first Adriatic finding of Speleogobius llorisi (Actinopterygii: Gobiiformes: Gobiidae). Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 49 (2), 181 - 184. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIEP / 02540" type="journal article" year="2019">Kovačić &amp; Glavičić 2019</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F61FFF6FC56FD09FAF0FD48" author="Duhau-Spielmann, M. &amp; Renoult, J. &amp; Louisy, P." box="[951,1296,655,681]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refId="ref53650" refString="Duhau-Spielmann, M., Renoult, J. &amp; Louisy, P. (2021) Signalisation de / Record of Speleogobius llorisi, 04 January 2021 (obs. 03 September 2020, photo  5836). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.). Available from: https: // www. fishwatch. org (accessed 4 August 2021)" type="url" year="2021">
Duhau-Spielmann 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FB6FFD09FB23FD48" box="[1166,1219,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
; J. Renoult, unpublished observation).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F61FFF6FF26FD51FB01FCD8" blockId="84.[151,1437,150,826]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
Geographic distribution. Northern Mediterranean, presently known from the Balearic Islands (Kovačić 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FA83FD51FA75FD10" box="[1378,1429,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2016) to the Aegean Sea (Engin 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FE18FD7DFDC9FCF4" box="[505,553,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2017), including 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F61FFF6FD10FD7DFCDDFCF4" box="[753,829,763,789]" name="France" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">France</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F61FFF6FCABFD7DFB74FCF4" author="Duhau-Spielmann, M. &amp; Renoult, J. &amp; Louisy, P." box="[842,1172,763,789]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refId="ref53650" refString="Duhau-Spielmann, M., Renoult, J. &amp; Louisy, P. (2021) Signalisation de / Record of Speleogobius llorisi, 04 January 2021 (obs. 03 September 2020, photo  5836). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.). Available from: https: // www. fishwatch. org (accessed 4 August 2021)" type="url" year="2021">
Duhau-Spielmann 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FBFCFD7DFBADFCF4" box="[1053,1101,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
; J. Renoult unpublished observation), 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F61FFF6FED0FC99FE92FCD8" box="[305,370,799,825]" name="Malta" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Malta</collectingCountry>
(
